data.description: Pre-Construction. To be built.  Pre-Construction To Be Built | Click, Print, Home - A 3D Concrete Printing Company presents the first luxury, 3D Printed Concrete Home in the state of Florida; the second of its type in the nation, following ICON’s ‘House Zero’ in Texas. In a great location close to MacDill, Picnic Island, St Pete and Tampa. Designed by Keith Plymale, Architect of San Francisco with curvature in the exterior walls to be resistant to hurricane force winds, the home is also flood and fire resistant with a goal of no wood used for any structural elements. 3D Concrete Printing (3DCP) also known as additive manufacturing, utilizes an automated process of seamlessly layering concrete via robotic arms and technology, creating a solid, monolithic and impressive structure, while also minimizing waste up to 95%. The home print will conform to the current Florida building codes as if it were masonry construction, only with the addition of 5000psi strong steel-reinforced concrete walls; that’s 4 times stronger than standard block! The design is a true open concept with high 10'+ ceilings throughout and features a living area open through to a dining room facing a 12' pocketing glass sliding door adjacent to the kitchen lit by LED fixtures. With sustainability in mind, the kitchen will feature solid wood cabinetry, walk-in pantry, quartz countertops, Energy Star dishwasher and high performance appliances. A central feature of the home is the curved guest bathroom which is cylindrical and doubles as a safe-room in the house for adverse wether conditions. The primary owner's retreat bedroom is generously sized with an en-suite bathroom featuring dual sinks and a large walk-in closet. Aluminum framed Hurricane Impact Glass windows throughout, (not all windows shown on renderings will come at this pricing, the full clerestory is an upgrade). With a laundry room and two additional large bedrooms both with walk-in closets, this house has everything you need. The home will feature a low pitch metal roof and an optional custom 3D garage that can be printed on site to suit your needs. We can also print just about anything you can think of- benches, planters, your name.. optional. Exterior finish can be optionally smoothed or the layers of concrete can be left showing it's 3D printed. The listing and renderings are designed to be a starting point for a conversation on how to finish this home. Options abound, finish the interior walls or leave the concrete layers exposed, polished concrete floors or perhaps LVP. CPH - 3D is offering a $5000 credit towards the buyer's solar installation project. The home will be printed using the proven COBOD BOD 2 concrete printer using Quickrete lab tested and approved 'concrete ink'. Do you like the 3D concept, but not the location? Reach out, this house can be printed on your own site. This listing has been entered as best as possible with data that reflects the proposed new home, all buyers must do their own due diligence.    The listing and renderings are designed to be a starting point for a conversation between buyer and seller on how to finish this home.
